<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph>
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34185" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Plagiolepis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Plagiolepis madecassa Forel" lsidName-HNS="Plagiolepis madecassa Forel" order="Hymenoptera" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="madecassa">Plagiolepis madecassa Forel</taxonomicName>
,
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph>
[[ worker ]]. Cette forme merite d'etre elevee au rang d'espece et d'etre separee de la 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34198" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Plagiolepis" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Uploaded - Plagiolepis pygmaea" lsidName-HNS="Uploaded - Plagiolepis pygmaea" order="Hymenoptera" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pygmaea">P. pygmaea</taxonomicName>
. Sa taille est plus svelte que celle de la 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34198" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Plagiolepis" genus.completionEvidence="missing" genus.completionRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Uploaded - Plagiolepis pygmaea" lsidName-HNS="Uploaded - Plagiolepis pygmaea" order="Hymenoptera" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pygmaea">pygmaea</taxonomicName>
, et le milieu du mesonotum est tres distinctement etrangle, de sorte que sa portion posterieure, jointe aux stigmates postmesonotaux est aussi longue que sa portion anterieure situee devant l'etranglement. Les yeux sont aussi situes au tiers anterieur de la tete et la ponctuation piligere du thorax et de la tete est bien plus distincte que chez la 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34198" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Plagiolepis" genus.completionEvidence="missing" genus.completionRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Uploaded - Plagiolepis pygmaea" lsidName-HNS="Uploaded - Plagiolepis pygmaea" order="Hymenoptera" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pygmaea">pygmaea</taxonomicName>
. L'abdomen a quelques soies rousses, grossieres, arrangees un peu en series.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph>Meme localite que les especes precedentes, chez les termites de terre. Les exemplaress du Mangoro sont presque hoirs, luisants, plus fonces que ceux d'Andrangoloaka.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
